               <head>Miscellaneous works on riddles, 10 items (a-j)</head>
               <msContents class="https://lccn.loc.gov/sh87001470 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006003807">
                  <summary>Miscellaneous collection of treatises on riddles, Persian language, religious polemic, lexicography, and divination by various authors. The volume is not dated, but items a, c, and g are individually dated, ranging from dates within the reign of <persName key="viaf_308694679" role="oth">Emperor Akbar II</persName>, 17 Jumādá II 1236-(16 Z̲ū al-Ḥijjah 1241)/22 March 1821-22 July 1826. Neat to rough scribal nastaʿlīq. Annotations and corrections in margins. Stamped foliation. Lacking original binding. Binding damaged, boards covered with marbled paper and brown leather edging; marbling delaminating and torn, exposing inner matter (possibly an Arabic religious work). Folios unbound; cropped, wormholes, later repairs. Condition fragile. This volume has been autographed several times by <placeName>Muḥammad Karīm Allāh</placeName>. 
                  </summary>
                  <msItem n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1213-item1">
                     <locus from="1r" to="5v">ff. 1r-5v</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item a. </p>
                        <p>Treatise in mas̲navī form on the methodology of creating cryptogrammatic and enigmatic poems or muʿammā, by the great Ṣūfī and poet, <persName key="ark:/81055/vdc_100166176979.0x000001 viaf_90042997" role="aut">Nūr al-Dīn ʿAbd al-Raḥmān Jāmī</persName> (d. 898/1492). This is one of four such works by this author on this subject, the present example being the last and shortest. 
                        </p>
                        <p>The work is dated by concluding verses to 890/1485. 
</p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 5v): completed by <persName key="person_f7211" role="scr">Karīm Allāh</persName> at dār al-salṭanah (sic) <placeName>Shāhjahānābād</placeName>, in the reign of <persName key="viaf_308694679" role="oth">Emperor Akbar II</persName>, Friday, 17 Jumādá II 1236/22 March 1821. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Neat scribal nastaʿlīq-i khafī. 
</p>
                        <p>Annotations in margins and in interlinear spaces.
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22222">Muʿammā-yi mukhtaṣar</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_22222">معمّاى مختصر</title>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100166176979.0x000001 viaf_90042997">Jāmī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100166176979.0x000001 viaf_90042997">جامى</persName>
                     </author>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="2" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1213-item2">
                     <locus from="6v" to="11v">ff. 6v-11v</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item b. </p>
                        <p>Untitled treatise on the methodology of creating cryptogrammatic and enigmatic poems or muʿammā based on common and proper nouns, with illustrations in prose and verse, by an unnamed author. </p>
                        <p>The work comprises a muqaddimah, sixteen aṣl, and a concluding khātimah. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                        <p>Neat scribal nastaʿlīq-i khafī. 
</p>
                        <p>The work is preceded by notes on poets including <persName key="ark:/81055/vdc_100166176928.0x000001 viaf_98930150" role="subject">Rūmī</persName> and <persName key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656922.0x000001 viaf_250727850" role="subject">Mīr Ḥusayn Nayshāpūrī</persName> (f. 6r). 
                        </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="3" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1213-item3">
                     <locus from="12v" to="61v">ff. 12v-61v</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item c. </p>
                        <p>Treatise on the methodology of creating cryptogrammatic and enigmatic poems or muʿammā on proper names, by <persName key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656436.0x000001 viaf_181760170" role="aut">Ghiyās̲ al-Dīn ʿAlī ibn ʿAlī Amīrān Iṣfahānī</persName>, based on the treatise <title>Qavāʿid-i muʿammayāt</title> of his master, the Timurid historian <persName key="viaf_95224252" role="ant">Sharaf al-Dīn ʿAlī Yazdī</persName> (d. 858/1454). 
                        </p>
                        <p>The work is dated to 888/1484 and dedicated to the Timurid ruler of Balkh, <persName key="person_f7545" role="dte">Shāh Abū al-Ghāzī Sulṭān Maḥmūd ibn Abū Saʿīd</persName> (d. 1494), a paternal uncle of the <persName key="viaf_97090468" role="oth">Emperor Bābur</persName> (d. 1530). 
                        </p>
                        <p>The work comprises a brief preface, nine sections termed ḥall, and a khātimah. 
</p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 61v): completed in the reign of <persName key="viaf_308694679" role="oth">Emperor Akbar II</persName>, 28 Rajab 1236/1 May 1821. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Neat scribal nastaʿlīq-i khafī. 
</p>
                        <p>Annotations in margins and in interlinear spaces. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656436.0x000001 viaf_181760170" type="supplied">Ghiyās̲ al-Dīn ʿAlī ibn Amīrān Iṣfahānī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656436.0x000001 viaf_181760170" type="supplied">غياث الدّين على ابن اميران اصفهانى</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22223">Ḥall-i muʿammā bar qānūn-i Mawlānā</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_22223">حلّ معمّا بر قانون مولانا</title>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="4" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1213-item4">
                     <locus from="62r" to="62v">f. 62</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="ara">Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item d. </p>
                        <p>Single leaf extracted from an unidentified Arabic treatise on geometry by an unnamed author. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                        <p>Spaces for diagrams left blank. 
</p>
                     </note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="5" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1213-item5">
                     <locus from="63r" to="69v">ff. 63r-69v</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item e. </p>
                        <p>Fragment of a treatise on Persian linguistics by an unnamed author. 
</p>
                        <p>Defective at beginning. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22224">Qavāʿid-i Fārsī</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_22224">قواعد فارسى</title>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="6" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1213-item6">
                     <locus from="70r" to="70v">f. 70</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item f. </p>
                        <p>Fragment of an unidentified divinatory treatise on the significance of children born on particular days of the week. 
</p>
                        <p>Defective at beginning. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                     </note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="7" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1213-item7">
                     <locus from="71r" to="98r">ff. 71r-98r</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item g. </p>
                        <p>Excerpt from the introduction of a treatise on Persian grammar, dealing with the pronunciation, character, and function of letters of the alphabet, by an unnamed author. 
</p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 98r): completed Sunday, 22 July 1826.
</p>
                        <p>Rough nastaʿlīq. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22225">Z̤avābiṭ-i Fārsī</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_22225">ضوابط فارسى</title>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="8" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1213-item8">
                     <locus from="99r" to="109v">ff. 99r-109v</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item h. </p>
                        <p>Untitled polemic treatise applying the concept of bidʿah or innovation in religion to the legitimacy of the practice of reciting the names of caliphs and subsequent rulers in the khuṭbah of Friday prayers, by an unnamed author. </p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                        <p>Occasional annotations in margins in European brownish iron gall ink. 
</p>
                        <p>Several passages has been deleted by the scribe and may indicate this is an early draft of the work. 
</p>
                     </note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="9" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1213-item9">
                     <locus from="111r" to="113v">ff. 111r-113v</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara urd">Persian, Arabic, and Urdu</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item i. </p>
                        <p>Untitled collection of recipes (some with medical uses) and terms with their equivalents in Hindavī, by an unnamed author. </p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. </p>
                     </note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="10" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1213-item10">
                     <locus from="114r" to="146r">ff. 114r-146r</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item j. </p>
                        <p>Fragment from a larger unidentified Arabic lexicographical treatise listing pharmacological and dietetic terms, with additional Persian comments added sporadically, by an unnamed author. 
</p>
                        <p>Defective, having lost at least eight folios from the beginning. 
</p>
                        <p>Stylised naskh for Arabic lemmata. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                  </msItem>
